+	 * On SN2 with a PLX PEX8111 bridge, CPU writes to VRAM go through
+	 * SHUB -> PIC -> PCI-X -> PLX -> PCIe -> GPU with no write-combining.
+	 * Each 4-byte store serializes through the SHUB's limited PIO slots,
+	 * making a 5MB framebuffer write take 10+ minutes. This affects ALL
+	 * VRAM BOs, even those in the "visible" region — visibility only means
+	 * the BAR window covers the address, not that access is fast.
+	 *
